On 1 June 2025, drones that were launched by the Ukrainian Main Directorate of Intelligence struck the military airfield 'Dyagilevo' in Ryazan. Russian military also shot down Ukrainian drones, causing the debris to fall over the city. No civilian casualties, 1 apartment building roof was damaged. Overall casualties unknown. At the airfield, at least 1 TU-22M3 aircraft was struck directly by an FPV-drone. This attack was part of the large scale operation of the Ukrainian Intelligence 'Pavutina' - Spider's Web (each event coded separately). According to the Ukrainian officials, 117 FPV-drones were utilized for the operation and that 34% of all Russian strategic cruise missile carriers - 41 Russian aircraft (including A-50 'Mainstays', Tu-95 'Bears', Tu-22M3 'Backfires', Tu-160 'Blackjacks' were destroyed across 5 regions. Russian MoD reported that there were no military casualties or destroyed vehicles across 5 regions. NATO counted 10-13 destroyed and 40 damaged aircraft.

On 1 June 2025, drones that were launched by an agent(s) of the Ukrainian Main Directorate of Intelligence struck the military airbase 'Belaya' in Sredniy (Usolskiy, Irkutsk). Local Governor stated that there were no civilian casualties and damages. Overall casualties unknown. The drones were launched from the inside of a truck that was parked at a local tire shop. An unidentified number of drones was intercepted by the Russian military and the random civilian passersby who attempted to down the drones with sticks and stones. This attack was part of the large scale operation of the Ukrainian Intelligence 'Pavutina' - Spider's Web (each event coded separately). According to the Ukrainian officials, 117 FPV-drones were utilized for the operation and that 34% of all Russian strategic cruise missile carriers - 41 Russian aircraft (including A-50 'Mainstays', Tu-95 'Bears', Tu-22M3 'Backfires', Tu-160 'Blackjacks' were destroyed across 5 regions. Satellite footage showed that at least 6 jets were destroyed at the 'Belaya' airfield. Russian MoD reported an unspecified number of aircraft damaged across Irkutsk and Murmansk regions, and that there were no military casualties or destroyed vehicles across 5 regions. NATO counted 10-13 destroyed and 40 damaged aircraft. This is a first recorded drone attack on the territory of the Irkutsk Oblast.

According to the Ukrainian officials, 117 FPV-drones were utilized for the operation and that 34% of all Russian strategic cruise missile carriers - 41 Russian aircraft (including A-50 'Mainstays', Tu-95 'Bears', Tu-22M3 'Backfires', Tu-160 'Blackjacks' were destroyed across 5 regions. Satellite footage showed that at least 3 jets were destroyed at the Olenya airfield. Russian MoD reported an unspecified number of aircraft damaged across Irkutsk and Murmansk regions, and that there were no military casualties or destroyed vehicles across 5 regions. NATO counted 10-13 destroyed and 40 damaged aircraft.
